descript.abstract: This dataset depicts the geographic location of medical hospitals in the County of San Diego. Medical hospitals are defined as hospitals having a General Acute Care License with a purview, principle service, of General Medical/ Surgical and/or Pediatric care.
descript.purpose: This dataset was created for the purpose of mapping and visualizing the location of hospitals in San Diego County as well as access to service or other analyses.

overview.eadetcit: FID- unique ID 0-18 Shape- vector format (point) OSHPD_ID- Office of Statewide Health Planning & Development ID# NAME- Hospital name ADDR- Street address CITY- City location ZIP_Code- Most recent zip code delineation PHONE- contact phone # Parent_FAC- parent hospital name Truama_CTR- Truama room level LIC_FAC Facility level LIC_TYPE- license type SRV_TYPE- practice service type ID- unique ID 1-19 Assembly - State Assembly Districts for SD County HHSA- HHSA Region for SD County SRA- Sub-Regional Area defined by the US Census Bureau Supervisor- Supervisorial district for SD County TRACT- Census Tract Numbers for SD County Page- Thomsa Brother's Page Number TBM-Thomas Brother's (C)2009
